                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4282: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Magruder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-04T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 4, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 4—5:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Department’s instruction No. 14, July 3, 2 p.m. Statement referred to by the
                    Department reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The proceeds of the German reparations appear under revenue, as there is
                            nothing definite yet regarding President Hoover’s proposal to postpone
                            the payment thereof for 1 year in connection with the inter-allied
                            debts. Inasmuch as we enter them under revenue, we likewise enter under
                            expenditures the 350,000 pounds sterling which, failing any agreement,
                            we shall have to pay to England from the installments falling due next
                            year. Should the postponement materialize, it will cost us some
                            thousands of contos which it is necessary to sacrifice, they say for the
                            good of Germany and of the world.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In consequence I have deferred action inasmuch as no decision has yet been taken
                    by Portugal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Magruder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
